parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Consumption and Catalytic Converter Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can cause the catalytic converter to fail, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing a fire hazard.
Engine knocking or rod noise can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: Knocking or rod noise from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling or Failure to Accelerate
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or failure to accelerate can cause a loss of control, leading to an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Leak or Low Oil Level
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leak or low oil level can cause engine damage, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing an accident.
Catalytic converter failure can cause a loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing a fire hazard.
The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to stall or catch fire, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The check engine light is on
the vehicle shakes when pressing the brakes
the engine makes a knocking noise
the vehicle emits smoke from the tailpipe
the vehicle has a strong odor of gasoline or burning oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can cause the catalytic converter to fail, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the engine makes a knocking noise
the vehicle emits smoke from the tailpipe
the vehicle has a strong odor of gasoline or burning oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or failure can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the engine makes a knocking noise
the vehicle emits smoke from the tailpipe
the vehicle has a strong odor of gasoline or burning oil.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, catch fire, or leave the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the battery warning light is illuminated
the oil warning light is illuminated
and the engine makes abnormal noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or emit excessive emissions, which can lead to accidents or environmental harm.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the catalytic converter warning light is illuminated
and the engine makes abnormal noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall, catch fire, or leave the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
and the oil warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights and electrical system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to operate, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The headlights flicker or turn off
and the electrical system warning light is illuminated.
